    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_492844724__task_003/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The microbeMASST web app displays query results in interactive taxonomic trees, which can be downloaded as HTML files... To create the final taxonomic tree, the JSON file of the complete microbeMASST taxonomic tree is filtered according to the results and converted into a D3 JavaScript object that can be visualized as an HTML file.",
      "asbval:note": "microbeMASST does produce visualizable summary outputs (interactive taxonomic trees, HTML files, JSON/D3 visualizations), but these are outputs from a single tool (microbeMASST), not from aggregating multiple domain-specific MASST variants. The card's claim implies cross-tool aggregation, which is not supported.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41564-023-01575-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Combined, visualizable summary artifact aggregating results from domain-specific MASST searches",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:18:00.030017+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_492844724__task_003/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card describes a meta-aggregation workflow ('metadataMASST') that combines outputs from multiple domain-specific MASST tools (plantMASST, tissueMASST, microbiomeMASST, foodMASST). The paper describes only microbeMASST, a single domain-specific tool for microbial metabolomics. No evidence of a higher-level aggregation framework or other MASST variants exists in the paper.",
        "The research question presupposes the existence of multiple MASST tools and a unified aggregation system. The paper focuses on the design, validation, and application of microbeMASST alone, with no mention of other MASST implementations or a cross-tool aggregation layer.",
        "The card's framing suggests a task about data integration across heterogeneous MASST outputs. The paper's actual scope is the development and application of a single taxonomically-informed MS search tool for microbial monocultures."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:18:00.030017+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/conditional-logic-implementation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "microbeMASST is a community-sourced tool that works within the GNPS ecosystem. Users can search tandem MS (MS/MS) spectra obtained from their experiments against the GNPS/MassIVE repository and retrieve matching samples exclusively acquired from extracts of bacterial, fungal or archaeal monocultures.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes microbeMASST as a single domain-specific tool for microbial samples. No evidence of conditional routing logic mapping to six domain-specific MASST variants (plantMASST, tissueMASST, microbiomeMASST, foodMASST, metadataMASST). Paper only discusses microbeMASST; other domain-specific MASST tools are not mentioned or described.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41564-023-01575-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "conditional-logic-implementation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
