    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/cross-reference-publication-linking/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "microbeMASST is a community-sourced tool that works within the GNPS ecosystem. Users can search tandem MS (MS/MS) spectra obtained from their experiments against the GNPS/MassIVE repository and retrieve matching samples exclusively acquired from extracts of bacterial, fungal or archaeal monocultures.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes microbeMASST as a tool and its integration with GNPS/MassIVE, but does not address the research question of extracting/validating publications from repository documentation or verifying linkage integrity. The paper IS itself the peer-reviewed publication for microbeMASST, but the task card's research question describes a meta-level skill (validating publications of tools), not the tool's functionality itself.",
