    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectrum-metadata-parsing/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "microbeMASST is a community-sourced tool that works within the GNPS ecosystem. Users can search tandem MS (MS/MS) spectra obtained from their experiments against the GNPS/MassIVE repository and retrieve matching samples exclusively acquired from extracts of bacterial, fungal or archaeal monocultures.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes microbeMASST as a single domain-specific tool for microbial spectra. The card claims a general metadata-parsing skill that routes to multiple domain-specific MASST variants (plantMASST, tissueMASST, microbiomeMASST, foodMASST, metadataMASST). Paper only documents microbeMASST; no evidence of conditional routing logic to other domain-specific MASST tools or a general metadata-parsing framework that dispatches across multiple domains.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41564-023-01575-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectrum-metadata-parsing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Extract and validate domain-context metadata from user-submitted mass spectra to enable conditional routing to the appropriate domain-specific MASST application",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:22:36.442581+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectrum-metadata-parsing/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Users can search tandem MS (MS/MS) spectra obtained from their experiments against the GNPS/MassIVE repository... Users can leverage microbeMASST Python code to perform batch searches of thousands of MS/MS spectra by providing either a formatted MS/MS file (.mgf) or a list of Universal Spectrum Identifiers (USIs)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms .mgf and USI input formats for microbeMASST only. No evidence of plantMASST, tissueMASST, microbiomeMASST, foodMASST, or metadataMASST tools existing or being mentioned in the paper. The card describes a multi-domain routing framework that is not documented in this paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41564-023-01575-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectrum-metadata-parsing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when a user submits one or more MS/MS spectra (via .mgf file, USI list, or direct upload) and the downstream analysis requires dispatching to a specific domain-specific MASST tool (microbeMASST, plantMASST, tissueMASST, microbiomeMASST, foodMASST, or metadataMASS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:22:36.442581+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectrum-metadata-parsing/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The microbeMASST web application was built using Dash and Flask open-source libraries for Python (https://github.com/mwang87/GNPS_MASST/blob/master/dash_microbemasst.py).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms GNPS_MASST repository exists and contains microbeMASST web app code. However, no evidence that it provides conditional routing logic to six domain-specific MASST tools or that those other tools exist. The repository link points to microbeMASST implementation only.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41564-023-01575-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectrum-metadata-parsing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNPS_MASST (https://github.com/mwang87/GNPS_MASST) \u2014 Underlying code repository and runtime environment for all six domain-specific MASST standalone web applications; provides conditional routing logic and Fast Search API integration",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:22:36.442581+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectrum-metadata-parsing/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "As of September 2023, microbeMASST includes 60,781 liquid chromatography (LC)\u2013MS/MS files comprising >100 million MS/MS spectra mapped to 541 strains, 1,336 species, 539 genera, 264 families, 109 orders, 41 classes and 16 phyla from the three domains of life: Bacteria, Archaea and Eukaryota",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms microbeMASST exists and covers microbial spectra. However, the paper states 16 phyla (not 20), 1,336 species (not 1,379), and three domains (Bacteria, Archaea, Eukaryota \u2014 not 8 kingdoms). The card's coverage statistics are inaccurate. No evidence of 'routing' logic; microbeMASST is presented as a standalone tool, not as one target in a conditional routing system.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41564-023-01575-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectrum-metadata-parsing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "microbeMASST (https://masst.gnps2.org/microbemasst/) \u2014 Domain-specific target for microbial spectra (8 kingdoms, 20 phyla, 1379 species coverage); routed to when metadata indicates microbial origin",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:22:36.442581+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
